FTS5 is SQLite's full-text search module. Create a virtual table with `USING fts5(col1, col2)` then query with `WHERE col1 MATCH ?`. In Bun use `bun:sqlite`:

```ts
const db = new Database('app.db');
db.exec('CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE docs USING fts5(title, body)');
const rows = db.query("SELECT * FROM docs WHERE docs MATCH ?").all('search term');
```

Always sanitize queries — FTS5 throws on `.`, `/`, `(` characters.
